Package com.whitespike.visionstructure

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractEnv
    Represents an abstract version of the raw data environment received.
    Blob
    Represents the pixels that make up a sense
    BlobCombinerThreadResult
    Represents the result of a parallel thread during blob combining
    BlobThreadResult
    Represents the blobs found from a certain row of a screenshot
    BoundingBox
    Represents the "collision box" that minimally contains a sense.
    ChangedPixelsBlobThreadResult
    Represents a row's result when finding changed pixels in order to update the env.
    ComparisonClass
    Represents an object used to store contenders when attempting to match a newly discovered sense to one from a previous iteration (in order to see if the same sense has moved, etc.).
    Env
    Represents the top level structure of the api, a digital representation of an environment generated by the raw data received.
    MinAndMaxes
    Represents the min/max x & y, average x & y, average RGB values of pixels in a blob.
    Orientation
    Represents the characteristics of a sense.
    OrientationChanges
    The sense's changes in orientation compared to the previous instance.
    Pixel
    Represents a pixel in the env.
    PixelChange
    Representation of what change happened between two touching pixels (on the edge of the sense's blob) (used in creating sense definition).
    PixelColorRange
    Represents the english name for the RGB value of the pixel (or sense).
    PixelOverallChange
    Represents the comparison between two consecutive pixel changes.
    PixelPosChange
    Represents the literal change between two consecutive pixels.
    RawEnv
    Represents the raw data that is used to generate an abstract env.
    Sense
    Represents an abstract object found using the raw env.
    SenseDefinition
    Represents the definition of a sense (determined through the outline).
    Util
    Encapsulates a variety of raw-env-info-getting and core-action-executing actions.
